Some legislators also wish to allow the repeal of federal laws if two thirds of the states object to them.
As members of Congress sought to propose amendments, they did not move faster than in previous years.
In the 111th Congress, the legislators proposed 77 such amendments and in the 110th Congress 66 such amendments.
This rate will be less than in the early 1990s, when members of Congress, according to the Library of the Senate, regularly proposed more than 150 amendments every two years.
