Introduction of the “golden rule” budget to the Constitution
The leadership of the large coalition of social Democrats and Christian Democrats in power in Austria decided on Tuesday to write a budget “gold rule” into the constitution in order to reduce the budget deficit and thus avoid a possible downgrading of Austria's public credit rating agencies (triple A).
