Migrants also make net profits in social security systems, giving an average of 1 per cent of the total budgets of European countries.
The World Labour Organization, for example, estimates that in Germany, when an immigrant arrives at the age of 30, an average of 150,000 euros will generate net profits (income minus expenditure) in the State budget.
Nicolas Sarkozy, at the beginning of his mandate, was about to get caught up in the missing growth points.
These teeth, which were used to deter immigrants, had exactly the opposite effect.
